<br>
To do a north wall break, you have everyone zone in one group at a time, or even better, one person at a time if everyone knows how to do it.   When you zone into the fear portal you head straight out with a sow and an invis.   As you run towards the fire ring, youll see on your right hand side a bridge of some sort with a bell near it.  You want to stay right by this bridge as you continue running to the firewall.   Be aware of any Scarelings, Shiverbacks, or spinechillers you see, they all have the ability to see invis, so avoid them at all cost.    When you reach the firewall turn to the left and follow the outside of the firewall arround until you reach the area where the firewall is closest to the north wall.   Camp out on the north wall, rince and repeat with everyone in the raid.    the key to making this tactic work is to get a cleric camped out in this spot.   This spot is fairly safe, no mobs will agro on you if you keep a tight camp.  Occationally a glare lord might path near by and agro on your camp if your not careful, but they dont pose much of a threat by themselves.<br>
<br>
Pulling Tactics without an enchanter...<br>
<br>
Easiest way to pull fear without an enchanter is to have one person with a run enhancing buff  (preferably a bard or paladin with holy steed) run out and grab a few mobs, then kite them arround.   This person needs to be able to refresh his/her run buff because if it fades and they cant refresh it quickly, they will die.     This person will kite the mobs arround in a very large circle, and have someone pick off of them when the circle brings them semi close to camp.   Remember the agro range in fear is HUGE, so be sure to have this kiter running circles a good ways away from camp.  Paladins make good pickers as well because if you use a long durration stun to pick, the kiter will have taken the other mobs away from the picked mob before the stun wears, thus lowering the chance that you get more then one with the pick.<br>
<br>
If your guild has a good ammount of 55+ wizards and mages you could try an AE fear break, the only problem with this is your going to need to borrow a couple of real good enchanters.   Its essentially the same thing as a west wall break, you just have a crazy paladin with divine aura go round up as many mobs as possible, and run them into camp.   Enchanters stun, wizards nuke, mobs die <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    Very fun!    I wouldnt recommend this unless you borrow some experienced enchanters.  I would have to say though, AE fear is the most fun, not to mention the quickest way to clear fear.   You can clear fear in an hour from start to finish with AE, where as the fastest I have seen it done using a non AE method is about 4 hours.  If your a tank, bring a good book though cause your going to feel pretty useless unless you are pulling.<br>
<br>
I hope this helps.<br>
