<br>
<br>
for you though without chanter you want to do the hall butt to safe spot.  run a melee in first head ne to the TT bridge. hug the TT cause they dont see invis. run north to firewall turn left hug the firewall. hop over to center of the firewall along the north wall. thats almost entirely safe. camp that melee out if he did it without agro. if not die at safe camp.  next run clerics in together have them invised with bind up.  they run same path bring agro. at safe camp they both bind and /q if they have agro. it sounds crazy but your raid cannot fail if you get a cleric bound a safe camp.  this is sooo important on your first raid of fear.  next just invis people up after the clerics camp and have them train safe camp. die at safe camp.  <br>
<br>
most people use a die in place on this north camp break in but i prefer to have everyone just die at safe camp and save the hour long corpse run.<br>
<br>
After that start rezzing... fairly safe spot.  shouldnt have any trouble. even if you do you got bound clerics.<br>
<br>
as far as pulling have someone try to single.  in the event that they cant single(double) then have them do the circle around teh nw corner. big circle.  and yes a bard (for speed) is a good choice.  <br>
<br>
one thing about the run path.  tell people NOT to avoid the TTs that you see when you run NE. avoiding them puts you in pathing range of the see invis stuff on the west wall.  thats where your failed runs come from.  <br>
<br>
<br>
but if you get mezzers then west wall seems more practical using the evac more then less strategy.<br>
