</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uharlan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Harlan</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wandering Knight</span><br>  Posts: 192<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/17/02 7:13:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=124.topic&index=36>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Bards</span><hr size=1> Don't forget about bards for Fear break ins. I helped get someone's corpse the other night in a very small group (someone had gone LD the day before during a CT raid and got back and died the next day).<br>
<br>
I brought my baby 53 bard instead of my paladin. We had a shaman to slow, an enchanter to help mez (though it wasn't neceessary) and only 1 or 2 other people (the naked person we needed the corpse for and a necro to summon).<br>
<br>
The enchatner and shaman tashed/malo'd everything and I kept 'em all mezzed with just my baby bard. I could easily keep 3 iced at a time myself for no maan cost - when we wanted to kill I charmed one and sicked it on another.<br>
<br>
We only killed 6 or 7 MOBs since we had no desire to farm armor, but the break-in was clean. We could have easily added more and cleared if we'd wanted.<br>
<br>
Harlan<br>
Zebuxoruk <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ueasirok.showPublicProfile?language=EN>easirok</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 22<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/17/02 9:34:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=124.topic&index=37>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bards</span><hr size=1> Use your highest level people to break. 60s preferred. Do not send your level 47 cleric in for break just because he can CH.<br>
<br>
You *really* need an enchanter for crowd control in the first few minutes of the break.<br>
<br>
For Tunare's sake, do NOT try anything but a West Wall break. I have been on uncounted &quot;janitorial&quot; Fear raids, clearing the zone just to make our way to the north wall to rez a hapless prior raid from an inexperienced raid party. If you have done the zone enough times to feel comfortable trying a north wall break, then maybe consider it... but I still believe a west break is the best.<br>
<br>
If Cazic Thule, or any of the three golems (Fright, Terror, Dread) are up,... then do NOT use feign death pulling tactics. 90% of the mobs in this zone roam, and they are all &quot;social&quot;. They pass aggro to each other. FD does not erase this passed aggro. Its only a matter of time before you end up dealing with repeated rezzes of your pullers due to Death Touch. Just send out a puller and whatever they aggro, bring it all to camp and mez. You will save a lot of time on rezzing and rebuffing pullers that way.<br>
<br>
For the break groups, you wont need a shaman for slows. Mobs simply wont last that long. You need all the damage output you can muster.<br>
<br>
Lastly, do not be too proud to ask for help if the shit hits the fan. If you wait two hours after a wipeout to try and get assistance on CR from another guild, you are gonna have to face eating a LOT of full exp loss deaths.<br>
 <p>Easirok Soulsavior<br>
<a target="_blank" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=53778">Easirok's Magelo Profile</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ujeet.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jeet</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_yellowspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 29<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/17/02 11:22:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=124.topic&index=38>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bards</span><hr size=1> The guy was asking for exotic methods of breaking fear....not hearing over and over you need chanters to break the zone (you don't, especially not after kunark). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usirderekdrygon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sir Derek Drygon</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wandering Knight</span><br>  Posts: 227<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/18/02 9:29:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=124.topic&index=39>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://champions.morpheus.net/pics/derek2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bards</span><hr size=1> I feel that north wall is slightly easier for a smaller raid force, you just need to know how to get to the north wall.  none of this bind loop crap, just get a cleric in there, and get him/her camped out.  You dont even need to have an enchanter to break it this way.<br>
